1
00:03:22,640 --> 00:03:25,920
Let's just say that Ake
wants to fire him quietly.

2
00:03:26,600 --> 00:03:28,520
Nobody can blame Ake for that.

3
00:03:28,600 --> 00:03:31,000
The pride that burdens your soul.

4
00:03:31,080 --> 00:03:32,240
Isn't it heavy?

5
00:03:32,320 --> 00:03:33,880
No matter how heavy it is,

6
00:03:33,960 --> 00:03:35,400
at the end of the day,

7
00:03:35,480 --> 00:03:37,280
I want the person I love
to be proud of me.

8
00:03:37,360 --> 00:03:40,120
PREVIOUSLY

9
00:03:41,080 --> 00:03:44,800
Bank has evidence to make Petch leave.

10
00:03:44,880 --> 00:03:49,480
I hope tomorrow is Petch's last day here.

11
00:03:49,560 --> 00:03:52,600
How could they arrest
the person who saved your son's life?

12
00:03:53,560 --> 00:03:54,400
What?

13
00:03:54,480 --> 00:03:55,960
Check on Shogun.

14
00:03:58,160 --> 00:04:00,000
I'm sorry, Petch.

15
00:04:01,640 --> 00:04:03,680
I have to do what you never expected.

16
00:04:06,520 --> 00:04:07,640
I'm happy for you.

17
00:04:07,720 --> 00:04:09,720
You and Bank finally cleared the air.

18
00:04:10,520 --> 00:04:12,080
I'm happier for them.

19
00:04:12,160 --> 00:04:14,000
Finally, Bank understands Shogun.

20
00:04:14,560 --> 00:04:16,079
You're quite empathetic.

21
00:04:17,279 --> 00:04:18,440
What do you mean?

22
00:04:21,200 --> 00:04:24,600
I mean, you seem to understand
people so well,

23
00:04:25,200 --> 00:04:27,400
but you don't seem
to understand Mr. Nop at all.

24
00:04:31,200 --> 00:04:34,000
You believe that Bank loves Shogun,

25
00:04:35,000 --> 00:04:38,680
and I believe that Mr. Nop loves you too.

26
00:04:41,960 --> 00:04:45,120
As for my family matters,
I know how to handle them.

27
00:04:47,480 --> 00:04:48,760
Petch.

28
00:04:49,440 --> 00:04:51,320
Then you should let your father know.

29
00:04:52,320 --> 00:04:56,280
Do you have any idea how much
the person left waiting misses you?

30
00:04:58,000 --> 00:04:59,160
Dao.

31
00:04:59,680 --> 00:05:01,160
I know you mean well.

32
00:05:02,120 --> 00:05:05,640
But could you please give me some slack
so that I could make my own decision?

33
00:05:06,240 --> 00:05:08,000
I'm not controlling you.

34
00:05:08,680 --> 00:05:10,440
I just want you to think about it.

35
00:05:11,040 --> 00:05:15,120
In juvie,
I spent countless hours thinking about it.

36
00:05:16,560 --> 00:05:17,760
So please.

37
00:05:18,920 --> 00:05:21,280
Don't make me hurt my dad again.

38
00:05:29,600 --> 00:05:31,240
Why are you so stubborn?

39
00:05:36,720 --> 00:05:39,040
<i>I haven't been</i>
<i>on this live stream for days.</i>

40
00:05:39,120 --> 00:05:42,000
<i>Do all my fans miss me?</i>

41
00:05:43,840 --> 00:05:47,040
Spam the heart button if you've missed me.

42
00:05:48,680 --> 00:05:49,560
Oh, hey.

43
00:05:49,640 --> 00:05:54,040
Nick said, "Do you have a boyfriend, Sai?"

44
00:05:55,040 --> 00:05:56,400
You make me blush.

45
00:05:57,040 --> 00:06:00,600
What should I answer? Should I--

46
00:06:00,680 --> 00:06:03,080
Oh, I don't have a boyfriend.

47
00:06:03,160 --> 00:06:05,080
That's correct.

48
00:06:05,680 --> 00:06:07,560
But I have a husband.

49
00:06:07,640 --> 00:06:09,960
That's correct.

50
00:06:11,040 --> 00:06:12,760
What? Dam!

51
00:06:12,840 --> 00:06:14,520
What the hell did you just say?

52
00:06:14,600 --> 00:06:16,480
Everyone, listen up.

53
00:06:16,560 --> 00:06:21,000
Let me tell you,
if you date a clingy girl like her,

54
00:06:21,560 --> 00:06:23,000
you're doomed.

55
00:06:24,520 --> 00:06:25,560
You're full of it!

56
00:06:25,640 --> 00:06:27,600
- Take this!
- Sai!

57
00:06:27,680 --> 00:06:29,440
- What's going on?
- Stop!

58
00:06:29,520 --> 00:06:30,720
- Sai. Dam.
- No!

59
00:06:31,400 --> 00:06:33,520
- Quit it. Sai, quit it.
- You!

60
00:06:36,360 --> 00:06:37,960
No!

61
00:06:38,040 --> 00:06:39,840
You've ruined my live stream!

62
00:06:43,080 --> 00:06:44,160
Dam!

63
00:06:44,240 --> 00:06:46,040
Why are you making me look bad?

64
00:06:46,120 --> 00:06:47,240
Sai.

65
00:06:47,320 --> 00:06:50,480
You said your heart
only belongs to Petch, didn't you?

66
00:06:51,160 --> 00:06:52,040
So?

67
00:06:52,120 --> 00:06:54,640
What's with those men online, huh?

68
00:06:55,960 --> 00:06:57,080
You're right.

69
00:06:57,160 --> 00:06:58,720
My heart belongs to Petch.

70
00:06:58,800 --> 00:07:01,120
But my charm belongs to them.

71
00:07:01,200 --> 00:07:05,560
- I just need to have fun with my charm.
- Right. Hold on a second.

72
00:07:08,640 --> 00:07:10,480
Do you want to throw up for real?

73
00:07:10,560 --> 00:07:12,800
- Stop it!
- Hey, Sai, quit it.

74
00:07:12,880 --> 00:07:13,920
That's enough, Sai.

75
00:07:14,760 --> 00:07:15,680
Sai.

76
00:07:15,760 --> 00:07:16,600
I'm…

77
00:07:16,680 --> 00:07:17,520
I'm thirsty.

78
00:07:19,000 --> 00:07:20,640
Can you fix me honey and limeade?

79
00:07:20,720 --> 00:07:21,840
My voice is cracking.

80
00:07:21,920 --> 00:07:22,800
Sure.

81
00:07:22,880 --> 00:07:24,120
I'll take care of it.

82
00:07:24,200 --> 00:07:26,440
I'll fix you honey and limeade right away.

83
00:07:27,960 --> 00:07:29,560
You'll be dead meat, Dam.

84
00:07:29,640 --> 00:07:31,000
This woman.

85
00:07:31,080 --> 00:07:33,600
That's a double standard, obviously.

86
00:07:33,680 --> 00:07:35,240
So, you…

87
00:07:36,240 --> 00:07:37,360
Where have you been?

88
00:07:42,600 --> 00:07:44,000
You mentioned the new song, didn't you?

89
00:07:45,200 --> 00:07:46,520
Sudden change of subject.

90
00:07:48,720 --> 00:07:51,920
Did you see Natedao?

91
00:07:55,520 --> 00:07:56,880
She's the boss.

92
00:07:56,960 --> 00:07:58,080
You shouldn't make fun of her.

93
00:07:58,680 --> 00:08:00,920
So, was I right or wrong?

94
00:08:04,400 --> 00:08:05,240
Do you want to practice?

95
00:08:07,040 --> 00:08:07,960
If not, I'll leave.

96
00:08:08,040 --> 00:08:11,680
All right. We will practice, sir.
Sit down, sir.

97
00:08:11,760 --> 00:08:13,440
Come on, I'm just teasing you.

98
00:08:16,440 --> 00:08:17,320
Let's start.

99
00:08:20,920 --> 00:08:23,360
Did you make an appointment
with a guy who will expose Petch?

100
00:08:25,080 --> 00:08:26,320
The appointment is confirmed, sir.

101
00:08:28,040 --> 00:08:29,880
I've made an appointment as you requested.

102
00:08:29,960 --> 00:08:31,760
Don't disappoint me.

103
00:08:31,840 --> 00:08:34,760
I think you should arrange
a party to celebrate.

104
00:08:35,480 --> 00:08:37,039
Because once the clock strikes 3:00 p.m.,

105
00:08:37,559 --> 00:08:38,559
Petch will be gone.

106
00:08:39,480 --> 00:08:40,720
That's not good.

107
00:09:08,400 --> 00:09:09,360
Bank.

108
00:09:09,440 --> 00:09:10,440
Natedao.

109
00:09:12,000 --> 00:09:13,560
How could you do this?

110
00:09:13,640 --> 00:09:14,840
Is there any humanity left in you?

111
00:09:16,640 --> 00:09:17,520
What are you saying?

112
00:09:17,600 --> 00:09:20,000
I know why you're here.

113
00:09:20,080 --> 00:09:21,560
Then you should step away.

114
00:09:21,640 --> 00:09:22,720
I have an appointment.

115
00:09:22,800 --> 00:09:24,160
- Wait.
- Natedao.

116
00:09:24,240 --> 00:09:25,400
Stop getting in my way.

117
00:09:26,720 --> 00:09:28,840
You said Petch was your friend,
didn't you?

118
00:09:28,920 --> 00:09:31,440
How could you
stab him in the back like this?

119
00:09:32,040 --> 00:09:33,000
What?

120
00:09:33,600 --> 00:09:35,000
What are you talking about?

121
00:09:35,800 --> 00:09:37,800
Petch was sent to juvie, wasn't he?

122
00:09:39,360 --> 00:09:40,320
See?

123
00:09:41,200 --> 00:09:42,600
I'm not going to frame him.

124
00:09:42,680 --> 00:09:43,680
I'll tell the truth.

125
00:09:45,560 --> 00:09:46,840
Bank.

126
00:09:46,920 --> 00:09:47,800
I'm begging you.

127
00:09:47,880 --> 00:09:48,760
Natedao.

128
00:09:48,840 --> 00:09:50,240
You should stay out of this.

129
00:09:51,160 --> 00:09:52,960
I can't wait to receive
the prize from Ake.

130
00:09:53,040 --> 00:09:54,200
He's quite the big spender.

131
00:09:54,720 --> 00:09:55,560
Leave.

132
00:09:56,400 --> 00:09:58,520
I'll pay you double.

133
00:10:02,720 --> 00:10:04,400
You're willing
to spend money for Petch too.

134
00:10:04,920 --> 00:10:06,000
Such a shame.

135
00:10:06,080 --> 00:10:07,400
I've already made a deal with Ake.

136
00:10:07,480 --> 00:10:08,480
Stay out of this.

137
00:10:12,200 --> 00:10:13,760
So selfish.

138
00:10:13,840 --> 00:10:16,040
Petch shouldn't have helped you.

139
00:10:25,760 --> 00:10:27,080
There you are.

140
00:10:27,160 --> 00:10:28,160
I'm here.

141
00:10:28,240 --> 00:10:29,440
Good.

142
00:10:29,520 --> 00:10:31,320
Ake will see you upstairs.

143
00:10:31,400 --> 00:10:32,640
All right.

144
00:10:39,240 --> 00:10:43,400
Here you are, tasty honey and limeade.

145
00:10:44,560 --> 00:10:46,000
What?

146
00:10:46,080 --> 00:10:47,440
Where are they?

147
00:10:53,680 --> 00:10:55,680
Dam must be the one who plotted this.

148
00:10:55,760 --> 00:10:58,080
He probably took Petch somewhere else.

149
00:11:00,440 --> 00:11:02,440
He'll see!

150
00:11:03,120 --> 00:11:04,640
Watch where you're walking.

151
00:11:04,720 --> 00:11:06,320
Sorry, I'm looking for Petch.

152
00:11:07,000 --> 00:11:07,960
He's not here.

153
00:11:08,040 --> 00:11:09,400
Where is he?

154
00:11:10,280 --> 00:11:12,080
I don't know either.

155
00:11:12,600 --> 00:11:13,640
Wait.

156
00:11:14,960 --> 00:11:16,640
Why are you looking for him?

157
00:11:16,720 --> 00:11:17,680
What's the matter?

158
00:11:17,760 --> 00:11:18,800
Step away.

159
00:11:18,880 --> 00:11:21,000
Give me the reason first.

160
00:11:22,080 --> 00:11:25,080
Fine. I'll tell you then.

161
00:11:25,160 --> 00:11:27,560
Someone was about to tell Ake
about Petch being in juvie.

162
00:11:27,640 --> 00:11:29,720
- What?
- Why are you being so loud?

163
00:11:29,800 --> 00:11:31,840
Do you want everyone here to know?

164
00:11:32,520 --> 00:11:34,160
I'm about to have a heart attack.

165
00:11:34,800 --> 00:11:37,960
Are you just going to let your fiancé
ruin Petch's life?

166
00:11:38,560 --> 00:11:40,480
I'm not the one to blame.

167
00:11:40,560 --> 00:11:42,240
Then what else can I do?

168
00:11:42,320 --> 00:11:45,600
If the truth comes out
and Petch finds out we lied,

169
00:11:45,680 --> 00:11:47,840
wouldn't that make things worse?

170
00:11:48,440 --> 00:11:49,320
Right now,

171
00:11:49,400 --> 00:11:51,560
we must delay Petch
so he doesn't face Ake.

172
00:11:51,640 --> 00:11:53,280
I'll take care of the rest.

173
00:11:54,280 --> 00:11:56,240
Petch and Dam must be backstage.

174
00:11:56,320 --> 00:11:57,360
We should hurry.

175
00:12:02,120 --> 00:12:03,040
Stop!

176
00:12:03,840 --> 00:12:06,120
Move! What do you want, Joke?

177
00:12:06,200 --> 00:12:07,480
No need to be in a rush.

178
00:12:07,560 --> 00:12:09,560
You're already in my heart.

179
00:12:10,880 --> 00:12:13,240
- That was smooth. Hey!
- You!

180
00:12:13,320 --> 00:12:14,560
- Easy!
- Take this!

181
00:12:14,640 --> 00:12:16,040
How dare you use a pick-up line with me?

182
00:12:16,120 --> 00:12:17,880
I've been planning this for so long.

183
00:12:17,960 --> 00:12:20,040
You're so aggressive.

184
00:12:20,120 --> 00:12:21,960
Was that a woman's fist or a man's?
That hurt so much!

185
00:12:22,040 --> 00:12:23,760
Enough, both of you.

186
00:12:23,840 --> 00:12:25,080
We should find Petch.

187
00:12:25,680 --> 00:12:27,040
What was that, ma'am?

188
00:12:27,120 --> 00:12:28,880
Petch?

189
00:12:28,960 --> 00:12:30,960
You don't have to look for him.

190
00:12:31,040 --> 00:12:32,080
Why?

191
00:12:32,160 --> 00:12:33,560
Do you know where he is?

192
00:12:37,400 --> 00:12:39,120
Enough already.

193
00:12:39,200 --> 00:12:41,280
- Just spill it!
- I'm going to!

194
00:12:41,360 --> 00:12:43,520
I will. Back off.

195
00:12:43,600 --> 00:12:45,400
I will have to choose violence again.

196
00:12:45,480 --> 00:12:48,520
Look. It's like this.

197
00:12:48,600 --> 00:12:50,000
I was about to collect a debt from Petch

198
00:12:50,080 --> 00:12:51,760
because he owes me money.

199
00:12:51,840 --> 00:12:53,440
But before I could even get to him,

200
00:12:53,520 --> 00:12:57,240
Ake ordered someone to drag Petch
and Damrong off to that room.

201
00:12:57,320 --> 00:12:59,200
- Right over there.
- Petch.

202
00:12:59,280 --> 00:13:00,560
Dao, let's hurry.

203
00:13:00,640 --> 00:13:02,640
Hold on.

204
00:13:02,720 --> 00:13:04,080
Where's the fire, sweetie?

205
00:13:04,160 --> 00:13:05,720
I've already told you where Petch is.

206
00:13:05,800 --> 00:13:07,120
Pay up. Twenty baht.

207
00:13:07,200 --> 00:13:10,320
- Joke, you little…
- No!

208
00:13:10,920 --> 00:13:11,760
Let's go, Dao.

209
00:13:11,840 --> 00:13:13,120
My family jewels.

210
00:13:14,960 --> 00:13:19,120
I didn't even get a chance to flirt,
and I'm already in agony. What?

211
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:20,600
Why are they in such a hurry?

212
00:13:20,680 --> 00:13:25,840
Are you sure, Bank,
that your evidence is solid?

213
00:13:25,920 --> 00:13:27,440
Of course.

214
00:13:27,520 --> 00:13:30,680
I guarantee today will be a day
you'll never forget.

215
00:13:32,160 --> 00:13:33,600
I can vouch for that too, sir.

216
00:13:33,680 --> 00:13:35,280
Bank is an old rival of Petch.

217
00:13:36,040 --> 00:13:37,080
Bank.

218
00:13:37,760 --> 00:13:39,080
Bring out the evidence.

219
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:43,400
I already told you.
I'll only reveal it in front of Petch.

220
00:13:47,560 --> 00:13:49,440
Then I'll be waiting to see.

221
00:13:49,520 --> 00:13:51,680
If your evidence
isn't actually that great,

222
00:13:52,720 --> 00:13:54,640
you won't get a single baht from me.

223
00:13:58,400 --> 00:13:59,440
Come in.

224
00:14:04,200 --> 00:14:05,760
I'm expecting to see you.

225
00:14:09,520 --> 00:14:10,520
Bank.

226
00:14:11,280 --> 00:14:13,560
Nice to see you again, buddy.

227
00:14:20,720 --> 00:14:21,680
Hurry up, Dao.

228
00:14:26,720 --> 00:14:27,880
What are you doing here?

229
00:14:29,000 --> 00:14:31,800
I don't know what this is about,
but something in this room…

230
00:14:32,520 --> 00:14:33,480
smells fishy.

231
00:14:33,560 --> 00:14:34,720
I bet it's nothing good.

232
00:14:34,800 --> 00:14:37,120
Your best friend here is a good guesser.

233
00:14:38,880 --> 00:14:40,040
Save the chatter.

234
00:14:40,120 --> 00:14:43,280
Bank, you can go ahead
and show us your evidence now.

235
00:14:43,360 --> 00:14:44,640
What evidence?

236
00:14:45,760 --> 00:14:48,720
- The evidence that you used to--
- Wait!

237
00:14:50,720 --> 00:14:52,200
Dao.

238
00:14:52,280 --> 00:14:53,360
Why did you come in?

239
00:14:55,360 --> 00:14:56,280
Sorry.

240
00:14:56,360 --> 00:14:57,480
It's just…

241
00:14:57,560 --> 00:14:59,760
I have an urgent matter
I need to discuss with you.

242
00:15:01,480 --> 00:15:02,760
What's the urgent matter?

243
00:15:05,080 --> 00:15:06,960
Well…

244
00:15:07,680 --> 00:15:08,600
Oh, right.

245
00:15:08,680 --> 00:15:11,760
The client's private party tomorrow,
right, ma'am?

246
00:15:11,840 --> 00:15:15,600
Yes! There are a lot of details
that I want to consult you about.

247
00:15:16,160 --> 00:15:18,040
Should we go talk in my office?

248
00:15:21,640 --> 00:15:22,600
All right, Dao.

249
00:15:23,920 --> 00:15:24,840
Great.

250
00:15:24,920 --> 00:15:26,960
In that case,
excuse us for a moment, everyone.

251
00:15:28,120 --> 00:15:29,400
I'll follow you in a bit.

252
00:15:31,880 --> 00:15:34,360
Let me clear up
an important matter here first.

253
00:15:35,040 --> 00:15:38,080
I think it's better
if you stay here with us, ma'am.

254
00:15:38,600 --> 00:15:40,400
We can all look
at this important evidence together.

255
00:15:43,080 --> 00:15:44,440
That's a good idea.

256
00:15:44,520 --> 00:15:47,400
Stay here and see
the important evidence with us.

257
00:15:48,880 --> 00:15:50,080
What is it?

258
00:15:50,160 --> 00:15:51,240
What evidence?

259
00:15:51,320 --> 00:15:52,280
Bank.

260
00:15:53,720 --> 00:15:54,680
Show us.

261
00:15:55,720 --> 00:15:58,680
Sir, I don't think
this man is trustworthy.

262
00:15:58,760 --> 00:16:00,200
Whoever interrupts me again

263
00:16:01,520 --> 00:16:02,800
is getting thrown out of this room.

264
00:16:08,920 --> 00:16:10,120
All right.

265
00:16:11,480 --> 00:16:13,480
I'm here to tell everyone the truth.

266
00:16:18,200 --> 00:16:20,840
This is my phone
from when I was in vocational college.

267
00:16:22,040 --> 00:16:25,280
I have an important audio clip saved here.

268
00:16:26,760 --> 00:16:28,440
I'm going to play it for everyone to hear,

269
00:16:29,440 --> 00:16:30,400
so we can decide whether Petch

270
00:16:31,240 --> 00:16:33,120
actually deserves to keep working here.

271
00:16:38,320 --> 00:16:40,040
<i>Do whatever it takes</i>

272
00:16:40,760 --> 00:16:42,440
<i>to kick Petch</i>

273
00:16:42,520 --> 00:16:44,440
<i>out of school.</i>

274
00:16:45,120 --> 00:16:48,560
<i>You want me to get him expelled?</i>

275
00:16:48,640 --> 00:16:49,720
<i>Yes.</i>

276
00:16:49,800 --> 00:16:51,280
<i>Make it happen</i>

277
00:16:52,720 --> 00:16:54,080
<i>and you will owe me nothing.</i>

278
00:16:55,920 --> 00:16:56,960
<i>Do you really mean that?</i>

279
00:16:58,920 --> 00:16:59,760
Enough!

280
00:16:59,840 --> 00:17:01,000
What?

281
00:17:01,080 --> 00:17:02,200
Why?

282
00:17:02,280 --> 00:17:04,480
I was just enjoying the radio show.

283
00:17:04,560 --> 00:17:05,760
Shut up!

284
00:17:06,400 --> 00:17:09,000
Bank, why the hell
did you play that crazy clip?

285
00:17:09,079 --> 00:17:10,720
It's not crazy at all.

286
00:17:11,359 --> 00:17:12,319
It's the truth

287
00:17:13,119 --> 00:17:16,240
about how you ordered us to frame Petch

288
00:17:16,319 --> 00:17:17,599
so he would get expelled from school.

289
00:17:17,680 --> 00:17:19,119
- Shut your damn mouth!
- No, sir!

290
00:17:21,079 --> 00:17:22,800
Mud, this is your fault!

291
00:17:22,880 --> 00:17:24,079
Why did you bring this loser here?

292
00:17:24,160 --> 00:17:25,599
Wow, what a sore loser.

293
00:17:25,680 --> 00:17:26,560
Shut it!

294
00:17:27,599 --> 00:17:28,560
Dao.

295
00:17:28,640 --> 00:17:30,920
It's not true. It's a fake clip.

296
00:17:31,000 --> 00:17:32,680
Then why are you acting so defensive?

297
00:17:33,640 --> 00:17:36,920
I never thought
you would be this kind of person.

298
00:17:37,000 --> 00:17:39,520
You used dirty tricks
to force Petch out of school.

299
00:17:40,240 --> 00:17:41,080
Dao.

300
00:17:41,880 --> 00:17:43,360
Why are you overthinking this?

301
00:17:43,920 --> 00:17:46,720
Back then,
Petch and I were still fighting.

302
00:17:47,360 --> 00:17:49,520
But we're good now.

303
00:17:49,600 --> 00:17:50,640
We've cleared things up, right?

304
00:17:52,240 --> 00:17:53,280
Yes.

305
00:17:54,120 --> 00:17:55,320
I don't hold a grudge.

306
00:17:56,600 --> 00:17:58,640
The past is the past. It can't be changed.

307
00:18:00,120 --> 00:18:01,560
See, Dao?

308
00:18:01,640 --> 00:18:03,000
We've already cleared things up.

309
00:18:03,080 --> 00:18:04,640
I wasn't finished.

310
00:18:06,640 --> 00:18:10,240
The past can't be changed,
but behavior can.

311
00:18:10,960 --> 00:18:13,040
If you know the difference
between right and wrong.

312
00:18:23,320 --> 00:18:24,240
Bank.

313
00:18:27,800 --> 00:18:31,160
Thank you so much
for helping keep Petch's secret.

314
00:18:31,840 --> 00:18:33,560
Besides, you totally humiliated Ake.

315
00:18:33,640 --> 00:18:35,040
I'm just lucky

316
00:18:35,120 --> 00:18:38,480
I held onto that clip Joe secretly
recorded of Ake and shared with me.

317
00:18:38,560 --> 00:18:40,560
But you're such a great actor.

318
00:18:41,120 --> 00:18:42,160
I've got to hand it to you.

319
00:18:42,240 --> 00:18:43,760
I had to.

320
00:18:43,840 --> 00:18:45,640
I didn't want Ake and his men
to catch on too early.

321
00:18:46,920 --> 00:18:47,960
Hey.

322
00:18:48,040 --> 00:18:51,800
What made you change your mind
and expose Ake instead of Petch?

323
00:18:52,360 --> 00:18:54,000
Ake was going to pay you too, wasn't he?

324
00:18:54,800 --> 00:18:55,640
The money…

325
00:18:56,480 --> 00:18:57,840
Everyone wants it, of course.

326
00:18:59,040 --> 00:19:00,520
But Petch's goodness

327
00:19:01,160 --> 00:19:02,680
is worth way more than that money.

328
00:19:03,840 --> 00:19:04,920
So, I've decided that

329
00:19:05,800 --> 00:19:08,960
I won't let myself be a tool
for bad people to hurt Petch anymore.

330
00:19:11,880 --> 00:19:13,080
That's wonderful.

331
00:19:14,120 --> 00:19:15,680
So you're both here.

332
00:19:15,760 --> 00:19:17,480
I was just looking for you.

333
00:19:18,640 --> 00:19:22,520
You're totally awesome for exposing
that arrogant jerk's true colors.

334
00:19:22,600 --> 00:19:24,080
I'm not awesome at all, man.

335
00:19:25,000 --> 00:19:26,200
I just wanted to make it up to Petch.

336
00:19:27,640 --> 00:19:29,560
I want you to know

337
00:19:30,440 --> 00:19:32,440
that I'm sorry for the terrible things
I did to you.

338
00:19:33,000 --> 00:19:34,400
Please forgive me, Petch.

339
00:19:35,000 --> 00:19:36,680
Friends don't hold grudges
against each other.

340
00:19:38,120 --> 00:19:39,520
We can forgive each other.

341
00:19:42,040 --> 00:19:43,560
Thanks, man.

342
00:19:43,640 --> 00:19:44,480
Come on.

343
00:19:45,200 --> 00:19:46,520
That's what friends do.

344
00:19:47,160 --> 00:19:50,400
I'm happy for both of my friends.

345
00:19:50,480 --> 00:19:54,880
Bank, Petch, you guys
finally worked things out. Awesome!

346
00:20:03,840 --> 00:20:07,560
Seeing you smile makes me happy too.

347
00:20:08,440 --> 00:20:09,760
Sweet dreams, Petch.

348
00:20:13,040 --> 00:20:14,720
YOU RECEIVED A NEW MESSAGE

349
00:20:16,280 --> 00:20:18,560
Did you really just send me a message?

350
00:20:21,080 --> 00:20:23,760
PETCH UNSENT A MESSAGE

351
00:20:25,360 --> 00:20:27,120
You unsent it.

352
00:20:30,480 --> 00:20:31,880
You're really crazy.

353
00:20:33,360 --> 00:20:35,520
But I'm even crazier for waiting for you.

354
00:20:41,240 --> 00:20:43,640
I will wait until the day
you open your heart.

355
00:21:43,800 --> 00:21:45,880
That's great. Come on.

356
00:21:46,760 --> 00:21:48,160
Yes.

357
00:21:50,200 --> 00:21:51,080
Right?

358
00:21:52,560 --> 00:21:54,880
Follow me, son. Come on.

359
00:21:54,960 --> 00:21:57,000
Yes.

360
00:22:00,000 --> 00:22:01,600
- Right.
- Like this?

361
00:22:04,240 --> 00:22:06,440
Cheers.

362
00:22:06,520 --> 00:22:09,320
Today, Petch and I
are hosting a celebration for you,

363
00:22:09,400 --> 00:22:11,520
father and son,
who finally worked things out.

364
00:22:12,200 --> 00:22:14,520
It's a shame Sai Kaew
couldn't come with us.

365
00:22:14,600 --> 00:22:17,600
But she sent some snacks for Shogun too.

366
00:22:18,680 --> 00:22:19,920
Bank, Shogun,

367
00:22:20,680 --> 00:22:22,280
we're really happy for you guys.

368
00:22:22,920 --> 00:22:24,640
Thanks.

369
00:22:24,720 --> 00:22:26,760
Shogun, say thank you to Mr. Petch.

370
00:22:29,120 --> 00:22:30,720
Thank you, Petch--

371
00:22:30,800 --> 00:22:32,920
- I mean Mr. Petch.
- Hey.

372
00:22:35,080 --> 00:22:37,160
Thank you for helping me with everything.

373
00:22:38,280 --> 00:22:41,120
And for buying me new shoes.

374
00:22:41,200 --> 00:22:42,720
I love them!

375
00:22:42,800 --> 00:22:43,880
I love them so much!

376
00:22:45,200 --> 00:22:48,520
As long as you like them, I'm happy.

377
00:22:48,600 --> 00:22:53,040
I'm planning to wear them

378
00:22:53,120 --> 00:22:55,600
to the dance competition in Phuket.

379
00:22:55,680 --> 00:22:57,960
What? Why are you going there, Shogun?

380
00:22:58,640 --> 00:23:00,560
I'm thinking of moving us down there.

381
00:23:01,480 --> 00:23:05,440
What? You and Shogun are moving to Phuket?

382
00:23:06,200 --> 00:23:07,360
Yes.

383
00:23:07,440 --> 00:23:11,040
My cousin works
at a yacht management company.

384
00:23:11,120 --> 00:23:14,560
They're looking for more mechanics,
so he asked me to work with him.

385
00:23:15,200 --> 00:23:17,760
The pay is pretty good.

386
00:23:17,840 --> 00:23:20,360
I figured that if I moved down there,

387
00:23:20,440 --> 00:23:23,400
I'd have enough money to send Shogun
to the dance classes he wants.

388
00:23:23,480 --> 00:23:25,120
Thank you, Dad.

389
00:23:25,200 --> 00:23:28,400
- I love you the most.
- I know.

390
00:23:28,480 --> 00:23:29,800
Save the sweet talk.

391
00:23:29,880 --> 00:23:31,320
I've invested this much,

392
00:23:31,400 --> 00:23:34,080
so you better be the star
of the dance floor, you hear?

393
00:23:34,160 --> 00:23:35,200
I promise.

394
00:23:35,280 --> 00:23:37,080
If there's a competition anywhere,

395
00:23:37,160 --> 00:23:40,400
I'll wear the shoes Mr. Petch bought me,

396
00:23:40,480 --> 00:23:44,080
dance my heart out,
and bring home a trophy for you.

397
00:23:44,160 --> 00:23:46,400
Right. Make sure you actually do it.

398
00:23:46,480 --> 00:23:48,400
Don't just brag about it, okay?

399
00:23:48,480 --> 00:23:50,040
You have to make it happen.

400
00:23:51,520 --> 00:23:53,840
If Dao heard that, she would be thrilled.

401
00:23:54,360 --> 00:23:57,520
She split the cost of the shoes with me,
half and half.

402
00:23:58,280 --> 00:24:00,760
Why didn't Natedao come with you?

403
00:24:02,720 --> 00:24:04,000
She told me this morning

404
00:24:04,600 --> 00:24:06,360
she was stuck in a meeting
at the head office,

405
00:24:07,000 --> 00:24:08,680
so she asked me to pass along
her congratulations.

406
00:24:10,000 --> 00:24:10,880
Hey.

407
00:24:10,960 --> 00:24:14,120
That sounds so lovey-dovey.

408
00:24:14,200 --> 00:24:15,320
Totally gives off couple vibes.

409
00:24:15,400 --> 00:24:16,880
Don't ruin her reputation, Dam.

410
00:24:18,360 --> 00:24:19,920
She already has a fiancé.

411
00:24:38,640 --> 00:24:39,840
Oh, Bank.

412
00:24:40,520 --> 00:24:41,400
What's up?

413
00:24:43,280 --> 00:24:45,240
Tell Natedao goodbye for me.

414
00:24:48,760 --> 00:24:50,240
Why me?

415
00:24:50,320 --> 00:24:51,680
You can ask Dam.

416
00:24:53,640 --> 00:24:55,120
Oh, come on.

417
00:24:55,920 --> 00:24:57,840
You have someone
so wonderful right beside you,

418
00:24:58,440 --> 00:24:59,800
but you keep running away.

419
00:25:00,480 --> 00:25:01,480
That's enough.

420
00:25:02,640 --> 00:25:04,320
If you're going to talk nonsense,

421
00:25:05,560 --> 00:25:06,720
let's not talk at all.

422
00:25:06,800 --> 00:25:09,160
Hey, hold on.

423
00:25:10,760 --> 00:25:12,520
Natedao is a good person.

424
00:25:13,600 --> 00:25:17,840
Don't let a good woman like her
fall into the hands of a scumbag like Ake.

425
00:25:17,920 --> 00:25:18,960
Bank.

426
00:25:19,560 --> 00:25:21,080
I know you mean well.

427
00:25:21,760 --> 00:25:24,960
But there are still many factors
that keep her out of my reach.

428
00:25:26,080 --> 00:25:27,600
Stop it.

429
00:25:29,480 --> 00:25:33,360
You told me to change my mindset
for the people I love, right?

430
00:25:39,320 --> 00:25:40,560
I would do anything.

431
00:25:41,760 --> 00:25:44,080
But if it means dragging a star like Dao
down to my level,

432
00:25:44,680 --> 00:25:45,760
I can't do that.

433
00:25:48,160 --> 00:25:49,560
Let me make this clear.

434
00:25:50,760 --> 00:25:52,480
I'm not backing down or giving up.

435
00:25:53,280 --> 00:25:55,120
I just can't move forward right now.

436
00:26:00,000 --> 00:26:01,320
Let's just say,

437
00:26:02,320 --> 00:26:04,880
if Ake ever breaks Dao's heart,

438
00:26:06,040 --> 00:26:07,280
I won't let him get away with it.

439
00:26:07,880 --> 00:26:09,240
Okay.

440
00:26:09,920 --> 00:26:11,600
True worth shines through anywhere.

441
00:26:12,920 --> 00:26:15,800
I'll be waiting to see the day
you overcome your obstacles.

442
00:26:16,960 --> 00:26:20,520
And I'll wait to see the day
you'll be happy with the woman you love.

443
00:26:21,200 --> 00:26:22,280
Okay?

444
00:26:22,920 --> 00:26:24,120
All right.

445
00:26:29,360 --> 00:26:31,400
No one is happy about everything,

446
00:26:31,480 --> 00:26:33,240
and no one is sad about everything.

447
00:26:34,320 --> 00:26:35,560
The same goes for me.

448
00:26:36,640 --> 00:26:38,080
Recently,

449
00:26:38,760 --> 00:26:41,080
I was glad to reunite with an old friend.

450
00:26:41,160 --> 00:26:43,080
But now, he has to go on a long journey.

451
00:26:45,000 --> 00:26:46,560
I wish you a safe trip

452
00:26:47,360 --> 00:26:48,840
and good luck.

453
00:26:49,440 --> 00:26:50,640
Until…

454
00:26:52,320 --> 00:26:53,600
we meet again.

455
00:27:17,560 --> 00:27:21,800
<i>Don't be afraid of goodbyes</i>

456
00:27:21,880 --> 00:27:24,600
<i>Don't be afraid of time passing by</i>

457
00:27:24,680 --> 00:27:27,520
<i>That is real love</i>

458
00:27:28,400 --> 00:27:32,760
<i>Don't be afraid of going alone</i>

459
00:27:32,840 --> 00:27:35,240
<i>You'll never be alone</i>

460
00:27:35,320 --> 00:27:38,400
<i>Just want you to know</i>

461
00:27:40,920 --> 00:27:46,000
<i>Out of this endless yearning</i>

462
00:27:46,080 --> 00:27:51,800
<i>Hold on, the wait won't be too long</i>

463
00:27:51,880 --> 00:27:56,600
<i>At the edge of the horizon</i>
<i>Where the fading light remains</i>

464
00:27:58,760 --> 00:28:01,880
<i>- We will meet again</i>
- Hey.

465
00:28:01,960 --> 00:28:03,600
- I'm his fan.
- Sir.

466
00:28:03,680 --> 00:28:04,640
I'll drink for him.

467
00:28:04,720 --> 00:28:06,960
- Hey, stay out of this!
<i>- Let your heart be your guide</i>

468
00:28:07,040 --> 00:28:08,520
- Sir--
- Screw you!

469
00:28:09,200 --> 00:28:10,720
Oh, no!

470
00:28:10,800 --> 00:28:12,240
Drink!

471
00:28:12,320 --> 00:28:14,080
I'm a fan, man!

472
00:28:14,160 --> 00:28:16,120
- No, sir. Thank you.
- Don't be arrogant!

473
00:28:16,200 --> 00:28:17,880
The customer is god!

474
00:28:17,960 --> 00:28:19,640
Hurry, that way.

475
00:28:20,400 --> 00:28:21,600
Hurry.

476
00:28:21,680 --> 00:28:23,640
This singer sucks.

477
00:28:24,320 --> 00:28:25,640
Damn you!

478
00:28:26,480 --> 00:28:28,080
- What the--
- Take him down now.

479
00:28:28,160 --> 00:28:29,600
Get down here.

480
00:28:29,680 --> 00:28:31,320
Hey! What the hell?

481
00:28:32,120 --> 00:28:33,400
Throw him out.

482
00:28:40,320 --> 00:28:41,840
Go home. You're too drunk.

483
00:28:41,920 --> 00:28:43,280
Petch, let's leave.

484
00:28:46,120 --> 00:28:48,520
Why the hell was he acting
like such a scumbag?

485
00:28:49,400 --> 00:28:51,280
Petch, wipe your face first.

486
00:28:52,560 --> 00:28:55,040
Too bad the guards dragged him away first.

487
00:28:55,120 --> 00:28:57,560
I would have torn him apart.

488
00:28:57,640 --> 00:29:00,640
Exactly. Who does he think he is,
the master of the universe?

489
00:29:00,720 --> 00:29:03,760
Musicians have dignity too, man.
He should show some respect.

490
00:29:03,840 --> 00:29:04,960
Yeah.

491
00:29:05,040 --> 00:29:06,280
Forget it.

492
00:29:07,880 --> 00:29:08,880
I'm going to the restroom.

493
00:29:08,960 --> 00:29:11,120
- I'm coming with you, Petch.
- Hey.

494
00:29:11,800 --> 00:29:12,920
Stay here.

495
00:29:13,000 --> 00:29:14,680
What now, Dam?

496
00:29:14,760 --> 00:29:17,200
Petch is going to the men's restroom.
Stay here.

497
00:29:17,920 --> 00:29:20,200
Again! You're so annoying!

498
00:29:22,600 --> 00:29:26,440
Take your eyes off her for a second,
and she's ready to harass a guy.

499
00:29:40,280 --> 00:29:41,560
How's it going, Petch?

500
00:29:46,360 --> 00:29:48,400
How does it feel

501
00:29:49,480 --> 00:29:50,880
to be looked down on?

502
00:29:51,480 --> 00:29:52,600
What now?

503
00:29:52,680 --> 00:29:53,960
I just wanted to know

504
00:29:55,400 --> 00:29:57,520
if it hurt a lot.

505
00:29:58,560 --> 00:30:00,520
Turns out my guy

506
00:30:01,600 --> 00:30:03,680
played his role a little too well.

507
00:30:05,240 --> 00:30:06,560
It really was your doing.

508
00:30:07,920 --> 00:30:09,600
I don't get it.

509
00:30:09,680 --> 00:30:11,040
Why are you doing this?

510
00:30:11,120 --> 00:30:13,000
You still have the nerve to ask?

511
00:30:14,760 --> 00:30:16,320
It's because

512
00:30:17,000 --> 00:30:18,320
I want you to realize

513
00:30:18,400 --> 00:30:19,680
just how low-class

514
00:30:21,160 --> 00:30:22,800
someone like you is.

515
00:30:25,400 --> 00:30:29,080
You completely lost face
when you got exposed in front of Dao.

516
00:30:31,120 --> 00:30:33,440
There's something seriously wrong
with the way your brain works.

517
00:30:34,080 --> 00:30:36,760
Because a guy who uses dirty tricks
to attack other people

518
00:30:37,880 --> 00:30:39,000
is truly low-class.

519
00:30:42,640 --> 00:30:44,120
A lowlife like you…

520
00:30:46,120 --> 00:30:48,120
shouldn't bring Dao down to his level.

521
00:30:49,160 --> 00:30:50,560
You'd better watch your back.

522
00:30:52,040 --> 00:30:54,600
I'll make sure

523
00:30:55,280 --> 00:30:57,080
you're out of her life forever.

524
00:31:34,840 --> 00:31:36,720
A lowlife like you…

525
00:31:38,120 --> 00:31:40,080
shouldn't bring Dao down to his level.

526
00:31:51,040 --> 00:31:53,320
INCOMING CALL: NATEDAO

527
00:32:03,000 --> 00:32:04,040
What is it?

528
00:32:04,920 --> 00:32:07,960
Wait. Why are you snapping at me?

529
00:32:08,800 --> 00:32:09,680
I'm not.

530
00:32:10,280 --> 00:32:12,440
If you have something to say, just say it.

531
00:32:13,200 --> 00:32:15,360
I went straight home
after my meeting today.

532
00:32:15,440 --> 00:32:16,800
I didn't go to the pub.

533
00:32:16,880 --> 00:32:18,960
So, I wanted to ask about Shogun and Bank.

534
00:32:19,560 --> 00:32:21,880
They both wanted to thank you
for buying shoes for Shogun.

535
00:32:22,440 --> 00:32:24,840
And they're moving to Phuket
at the end of this month.

536
00:32:25,520 --> 00:32:27,880
What? They're moving already?

537
00:32:27,960 --> 00:32:29,440
Are they still short on--

538
00:32:34,280 --> 00:32:36,240
You dare hang up on me, Petch?

539
00:32:36,320 --> 00:32:37,880
You think you can just do that?

540
00:32:51,800 --> 00:32:55,480
SO YOU'RE GIVING ME
THE SILENT TREATMENT NOW?

541
00:33:00,760 --> 00:33:02,520
YES.

542
00:33:05,280 --> 00:33:06,240
You jerk.

543
00:33:07,160 --> 00:33:10,520
Fine. I won't care about you
anymore either.

544
00:33:19,440 --> 00:33:21,000
There you are!

545
00:33:21,080 --> 00:33:22,360
You broke singer.

546
00:33:22,440 --> 00:33:25,120
You're right here.
I've been looking for you for ages.

547
00:33:28,760 --> 00:33:30,200
Hey, hold on!

548
00:33:32,000 --> 00:33:34,720
Let's talk first.
Where are you rushing off to? Let's talk.

549
00:33:36,760 --> 00:33:39,640
Sorry, man.
I'm not in the mood to talk to anyone.

550
00:33:40,480 --> 00:33:41,760
Not in the mood to talk?

551
00:33:41,840 --> 00:33:43,640
Feeling lonely? Sad?

552
00:33:43,720 --> 00:33:46,200
Or is it about love?

553
00:33:46,280 --> 00:33:48,840
Wait. Are you heartbroken?

554
00:33:48,920 --> 00:33:51,160
Don't tell me your girlfriend dumped you.

555
00:33:51,240 --> 00:33:53,640
No! Don't hurt me.

556
00:33:53,720 --> 00:33:56,320
I haven't done anything wrong.

557
00:33:56,400 --> 00:33:58,120
I'm looking away now. See?

558
00:33:58,200 --> 00:34:01,080
Just don't punch me.
I won't stand the fight.

559
00:34:01,160 --> 00:34:04,040
Please go easy on me, please.

560
00:34:04,840 --> 00:34:05,840
Why is he so quiet?

561
00:34:05,920 --> 00:34:07,960
Wait. What?

562
00:34:08,040 --> 00:34:09,080
Hey!

563
00:34:09,960 --> 00:34:10,960
Heck!

564
00:34:12,080 --> 00:34:14,800
Such a coward!
I thought you were so tough.

565
00:34:14,880 --> 00:34:18,719
I was acting scared to test you.

566
00:34:20,480 --> 00:34:22,400
Wow!

567
00:34:22,960 --> 00:34:24,239
That's great, Uncle.

568
00:34:24,320 --> 00:34:28,400
Thanks a lot, Ake, for keeping me company.
Let's call it a day.

569
00:34:28,480 --> 00:34:29,760
All right.

570
00:34:30,440 --> 00:34:33,480
In that case,
may I treat you to some coffee?

571
00:34:33,560 --> 00:34:35,000
- Okay.
- Consider it…

572
00:34:35,080 --> 00:34:36,800
a celebration of your top form today.

573
00:34:36,880 --> 00:34:38,480
Sure. Thanks.

574
00:34:38,560 --> 00:34:40,400
Let's head out then.

575
00:34:48,600 --> 00:34:50,040
Uncle.

576
00:34:50,120 --> 00:34:52,239
What are you looking at?
Your coffee is getting cold.

577
00:34:52,320 --> 00:34:55,520
Oh, hold on.

578
00:35:05,760 --> 00:35:07,440
Here, Ake. Take a look.

579
00:35:07,520 --> 00:35:10,440
This guy is going to be our new artist.

580
00:35:16,520 --> 00:35:22,080
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

581
00:35:22,160 --> 00:35:27,080
<i>- I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>
- How is he? Are you speechless?

582
00:35:27,160 --> 00:35:29,160
This guy sings really well.

583
00:35:29,240 --> 00:35:32,280
<i>- For my heart is crying out my love</i>
- Uncle.

584
00:35:32,360 --> 00:35:36,000
I don't think he has much of an aura.

585
00:35:37,160 --> 00:35:38,520
And besides…

586
00:35:39,840 --> 00:35:44,640
- This style of music probably won't sell.
<i>- I know that it simply cannot be</i>

587
00:35:44,720 --> 00:35:46,560
Look at the view count.

588
00:35:47,120 --> 00:35:48,160
There's barely any.

589
00:35:53,080 --> 00:35:56,400
But I think he has the potential
to be a superstar.

590
00:35:57,680 --> 00:36:01,600
Just add some production value
and a little bit of marketing strategy,

591
00:36:01,680 --> 00:36:02,960
and he'll be a massive hit.

592
00:36:05,640 --> 00:36:10,640
I love watching these cover songs,
and this suddenly popped up.

593
00:36:11,520 --> 00:36:13,240
Must be destiny.

594
00:36:14,520 --> 00:36:16,000
- Ake.
- Yes?

595
00:36:16,080 --> 00:36:18,600
Track this guy down immediately.

596
00:36:19,440 --> 00:36:21,720
I want him to release a single
under our label.

597
00:36:31,080 --> 00:36:32,160
Uncle.

598
00:36:32,240 --> 00:36:35,040
Well, let's play another round soon.

599
00:36:35,120 --> 00:36:38,000
Okay, sure. Don't forget what I asked you.

600
00:36:38,800 --> 00:36:39,880
I won't.

601
00:36:39,960 --> 00:36:42,040
I'll get this sorted out for you
as fast as possible.

602
00:36:42,800 --> 00:36:43,720
Thanks a lot.

603
00:36:43,800 --> 00:36:45,040
Goodbye.

604
00:36:50,800 --> 00:36:52,080
Petch.

605
00:36:58,760 --> 00:37:00,080
Mud.

606
00:37:00,160 --> 00:37:03,960
Find a highly skilled hacker
to take down Petch's channel right now.

607
00:37:04,040 --> 00:37:05,440
Don't ever let him shine.

608
00:37:12,920 --> 00:37:16,640
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

609
00:37:16,720 --> 00:37:19,440
Wow, Mr. Subpar-star!

610
00:37:19,520 --> 00:37:22,280
I mean, Superstar. There you are.

611
00:37:22,880 --> 00:37:25,400
People are trying to practice here.

612
00:37:25,480 --> 00:37:27,080
Can you not bother us, Joke?

613
00:37:27,680 --> 00:37:28,560
No can do.

614
00:37:29,680 --> 00:37:30,760
You asshole.

615
00:37:30,840 --> 00:37:32,960
Dam, let's not start a fight.

616
00:37:33,840 --> 00:37:34,880
Just look at how he treats us.

617
00:37:35,600 --> 00:37:36,480
I'll knee him!

618
00:37:39,680 --> 00:37:41,240
Don't do that.

619
00:37:41,320 --> 00:37:44,120
Don't do this to your creditor.

620
00:37:44,200 --> 00:37:45,720
What do you mean by that?

621
00:37:45,800 --> 00:37:46,960
Well,

622
00:37:47,720 --> 00:37:49,240
ask your friend then.

623
00:37:49,320 --> 00:37:53,280
Petch, you still owe me
for the suit rental.

624
00:37:53,360 --> 00:37:55,440
Pay up. Hurry.

625
00:37:57,920 --> 00:37:58,920
Two hundred, right?

626
00:38:01,280 --> 00:38:02,600
No.

627
00:38:02,680 --> 00:38:03,520
It's 1,000.

628
00:38:03,600 --> 00:38:05,240
Stop messing around.

629
00:38:05,320 --> 00:38:06,840
You said it was 200 that day.

630
00:38:07,880 --> 00:38:09,400
How did it magically grow to 1,000?

631
00:38:10,000 --> 00:38:11,280
Hey.

632
00:38:11,360 --> 00:38:13,760
Ever heard of interest?

633
00:38:13,840 --> 00:38:16,600
Overdue payments go up, obviously.

634
00:38:16,680 --> 00:38:18,160
Hurry up. Pay it.

635
00:38:18,240 --> 00:38:19,520
What's your problem?

636
00:38:19,600 --> 00:38:21,480
- Want to take this outside?
- He's not worth it.

637
00:38:23,400 --> 00:38:24,480
All right?

638
00:38:28,840 --> 00:38:29,760
I only have 200 for you.

639
00:38:31,120 --> 00:38:34,120
Take it or leave it
because I'm not paying any more.

640
00:38:36,680 --> 00:38:38,320
Holding onto cash

641
00:38:38,400 --> 00:38:40,280
is better than holding on to grudges

642
00:38:40,360 --> 00:38:42,800
against pathetic debtors like you guys.

643
00:38:43,600 --> 00:38:45,120
You just won't shut up.

644
00:38:45,200 --> 00:38:49,160
If we ever get famous,
don't you dare claim you know us.

645
00:38:49,240 --> 00:38:51,400
You guys? Famous?

646
00:38:51,480 --> 00:38:53,240
Are you dreaming?

647
00:38:53,320 --> 00:38:55,960
No way. You're completely delusional.

648
00:38:56,040 --> 00:38:59,880
At the very least, Petch's song
already has hundreds of views.

649
00:38:59,960 --> 00:39:00,800
Look.

650
00:39:02,680 --> 00:39:03,520
What…

651
00:39:03,600 --> 00:39:05,280
What kind of joke is this, huh?

652
00:39:05,360 --> 00:39:06,600
What's with the buffalo?

653
00:39:06,680 --> 00:39:08,440
It's nothing but buffalo.

654
00:39:11,560 --> 00:39:12,480
Wait.

655
00:39:12,560 --> 00:39:13,800
Petch.

656
00:39:14,560 --> 00:39:16,880
Our clip is covered with buffalo faces.

657
00:39:24,560 --> 00:39:26,320
I can't log into my account either.

658
00:39:27,760 --> 00:39:29,080
Petch!

659
00:39:29,160 --> 00:39:30,000
This is bad!

660
00:39:30,720 --> 00:39:32,120
I don't know what's wrong
with your channel.

661
00:39:32,200 --> 00:39:33,960
I can't watch anything!

662
00:39:34,800 --> 00:39:35,800
I think I know why.

663
00:39:36,640 --> 00:39:37,880
Our channel probably got hacked.

664
00:39:37,960 --> 00:39:39,000
- Hacked?
- Hacked?

665
00:39:39,080 --> 00:39:40,440
I can't believe this.

666
00:39:40,520 --> 00:39:41,800
Hey.

667
00:39:41,880 --> 00:39:44,880
Who would bother hacking
neighborhood nobodies like you?

668
00:39:44,960 --> 00:39:45,960
Aren't you imagining things?

669
00:39:50,920 --> 00:39:53,480
Job done. Petch's channel
is out of commission now.

670
00:39:54,360 --> 00:39:56,920
All the data on the channel
will vanish too.

671
00:39:58,360 --> 00:39:59,480
Very good.

672
00:40:00,320 --> 00:40:01,640
You live up to the rumors.

673
00:40:01,720 --> 00:40:02,600
Here.

674
00:40:03,640 --> 00:40:05,200
Your payment.

675
00:40:05,280 --> 00:40:06,120
Oh, wow.

676
00:40:07,080 --> 00:40:09,080
This pays so well.

677
00:40:09,160 --> 00:40:11,840
Whenever you have another job like this,
you can call me.

678
00:40:11,920 --> 00:40:13,640
Keep monitoring Petch.

679
00:40:13,720 --> 00:40:16,360
If his channel ever opens back up,
take it down.

680
00:40:17,360 --> 00:40:20,320
I promise you'll be paid handsomely.

681
00:40:20,400 --> 00:40:21,440
You got it.

682
00:40:27,680 --> 00:40:28,520
Hello, sir?

683
00:40:28,600 --> 00:40:30,160
Any updates?

684
00:40:30,240 --> 00:40:31,680
<i>All done, sir.</i>

685
00:40:31,760 --> 00:40:33,280
<i>I guarantee that from now on,</i>

686
00:40:33,360 --> 00:40:36,200
Mr. Sompob will never find
Petch's channel again.

687
00:40:37,320 --> 00:40:39,560
Good. But that's not enough.

688
00:40:39,640 --> 00:40:41,040
I want him to suffer more.

689
00:40:41,880 --> 00:40:44,080
<i>- What else do you want me to do, sir?</i>
- Mud.

690
00:40:44,160 --> 00:40:46,000
Send some guys to beat him to a pulp.

691
00:40:46,600 --> 00:40:48,360
I want to see him bleed.

692
00:40:54,840 --> 00:40:57,760
Here you are.

693
00:41:00,520 --> 00:41:02,960
Honey and limeade soothe the vocal cords.

694
00:41:03,040 --> 00:41:05,160
But if you want someone
to soothe your heart,

695
00:41:05,240 --> 00:41:06,840
it has to be me.

696
00:41:09,200 --> 00:41:11,360
What? What is this, Petch?

697
00:41:11,440 --> 00:41:14,760
I created one pick-up line for you,
but you didn't even get it.

698
00:41:16,720 --> 00:41:17,560
Petch!

699
00:41:17,640 --> 00:41:19,000
Petch!

700
00:41:20,000 --> 00:41:21,200
What is it, Sai?

701
00:41:23,600 --> 00:41:24,800
Just because the channel got hacked,

702
00:41:24,880 --> 00:41:28,240
you can't eat
and won't even answer when spoken to?

703
00:41:28,320 --> 00:41:29,720
No.

704
00:41:29,800 --> 00:41:31,560
I'm not giving up that easily, Sai.

705
00:41:32,400 --> 00:41:34,040
I was just thinking,

706
00:41:34,120 --> 00:41:36,280
if we start a new channel,

707
00:41:36,360 --> 00:41:37,600
what should we improve?

708
00:41:39,800 --> 00:41:41,880
Man! This sucks!

709
00:41:42,560 --> 00:41:45,040
What are you yelling about now?
What's gotten into you?

710
00:41:45,120 --> 00:41:46,600
Annoying.

711
00:41:46,680 --> 00:41:48,320
I'm done. Whatever!

712
00:41:48,400 --> 00:41:49,680
- Whatever!
- Hey.

713
00:41:49,760 --> 00:41:51,680
Hey, Dam. Calm down, man.

714
00:41:52,360 --> 00:41:53,600
Listen, Petch.

715
00:41:53,680 --> 00:41:57,000
Rerecording, reshooting,
and reediting everything isn't easy.

716
00:41:57,080 --> 00:42:00,120
And what if we rerecord it
and the vibe just isn't the same?

717
00:42:02,400 --> 00:42:04,720
You can be discouraged,
but don't back down.

718
00:42:04,800 --> 00:42:06,640
Even if we get hacked
a hundred more times,

719
00:42:06,720 --> 00:42:08,280
I'll rebuild it a hundred more times.

720
00:42:09,400 --> 00:42:11,680
I just feel like it's such a waste.

721
00:42:12,280 --> 00:42:14,120
Don't cry over spilled milk.

722
00:42:14,840 --> 00:42:15,760
Dam.

723
00:42:16,440 --> 00:42:20,600
Let's rethink and rebuild this.
Let's make it better than before.

724
00:42:22,000 --> 00:42:23,360
So true.

725
00:42:23,440 --> 00:42:26,080
How can someone be so sharp and handsome?

726
00:42:26,160 --> 00:42:28,680
You've completely won my heart.

727
00:42:28,760 --> 00:42:31,800
- Get over here.
- Ouch!

728
00:42:31,880 --> 00:42:33,880
I can't leave you alone for a second.

729
00:42:33,960 --> 00:42:37,800
Dam! What is wrong with you?
You're always blocking my moments!

730
00:42:37,880 --> 00:42:41,600
All right, you two keep arguing.
I'm going to practice guitar.

731
00:42:41,680 --> 00:42:43,160
You go on ahead, Petch.

732
00:42:43,240 --> 00:42:47,160
I'm going to teach this one a lesson
and straighten her out myself!

733
00:42:47,240 --> 00:42:50,080
- Go on then.
- You're so stubborn.

734
00:43:12,640 --> 00:43:13,680
Hey, Dam.

735
00:43:14,200 --> 00:43:15,080
Sorry, man.

736
00:43:16,000 --> 00:43:17,320
Let's do it tomorrow.

737
00:43:17,920 --> 00:43:19,280
I've got some errands to run.

738
00:43:19,360 --> 00:43:20,880
Where are you going?

739
00:43:21,920 --> 00:43:23,400
Don't worry about it.

740
00:43:23,480 --> 00:43:24,760
I'll meet you at the pub.

741
00:43:24,840 --> 00:43:27,040
And grab my guitar for me, will you?

742
00:43:27,120 --> 00:43:29,040
Petch, I'm coming with you!

743
00:43:29,120 --> 00:43:30,320
- Hey!
- What?

744
00:43:30,400 --> 00:43:34,040
Don't be so nosy.
You're just going to end up getting hurt.

745
00:43:34,120 --> 00:43:37,880
I'm going to get hurt because I have
an ungrateful brother like you.

746
00:43:37,960 --> 00:43:41,080
You never support your sister.
You always crush my dreams.

747
00:43:41,160 --> 00:43:43,960
I'm afraid you're going to get
your heart broken.

748
00:43:44,040 --> 00:43:45,800
Understand, you stupid kid?

749
00:43:46,760 --> 00:43:48,160
I'm not a kid anymore!

750
00:43:48,240 --> 00:43:50,200
How do you know I'll get my heart broken?

751
00:43:50,280 --> 00:43:52,680
You piss me off.

752
00:43:52,760 --> 00:43:58,360
Petch's heart is already taken,
you stupid kid!

753
00:43:59,400 --> 00:44:02,120
Dam, don't even try to scare me.

754
00:44:02,200 --> 00:44:04,560
If he doesn't have anyone,
and I don't have a boyfriend,

755
00:44:04,640 --> 00:44:06,400
that means I still have a chance!

756
00:44:12,800 --> 00:44:15,440
GRANDMA LOT'S GRILLED PORK SKEWERS

757
00:44:21,080 --> 00:44:21,960
Dad.

758
00:44:22,680 --> 00:44:24,840
I bought your favorite
grilled pork skewers.

759
00:44:26,400 --> 00:44:27,920
Oh, my son.

760
00:44:28,000 --> 00:44:30,760
You really know me so well.
This is my absolute favorite.

761
00:44:31,440 --> 00:44:33,160
You have to eat it all then.

762
00:44:33,240 --> 00:44:34,800
Thank you very much, son.

763
00:44:34,880 --> 00:44:36,400
Sir.

764
00:44:36,480 --> 00:44:38,560
How many grilled pork skewers do you need?

765
00:44:39,320 --> 00:44:42,520
I'd like ten grilled pork skewers
and two sticky rice, please.

766
00:45:11,200 --> 00:45:13,800
If you miss your dad,
why don't you live with him?

767
00:45:20,080 --> 00:45:21,560
Wait. Don't go just yet.

768
00:45:24,520 --> 00:45:27,240
It's my family's issue.
Can you just stay out of it?

769
00:45:28,600 --> 00:45:32,560
I'm sorry that I can't stand
watching you act out like this.

770
00:45:34,280 --> 00:45:36,320
You don't know the whole story.
You should be quiet.

771
00:45:38,560 --> 00:45:39,640
Petch.

772
00:45:41,280 --> 00:45:42,320
Please.

773
00:45:42,840 --> 00:45:45,240
This is my business.
I can handle it myself.

774
00:45:46,800 --> 00:45:47,960
Behind you.

775
00:45:52,640 --> 00:45:53,560
Dao, run!

776
00:45:53,640 --> 00:45:55,520
- Dao!
- Follow him!

777
00:46:00,120 --> 00:46:01,920
Where is he?

778
00:46:02,000 --> 00:46:02,840
You go that way!

779
00:46:03,640 --> 00:46:04,920
I'll go this way!

780
00:46:14,600 --> 00:46:15,800
You!

781
00:46:16,480 --> 00:46:17,520
Hey!

782
00:46:18,120 --> 00:46:19,680
Dao, step back.

783
00:46:25,200 --> 00:46:27,560
Watch out! Petch!

784
00:46:48,840 --> 00:46:49,720
Who sent you?

785
00:46:49,800 --> 00:46:51,240
Who sent you?

786
00:46:52,040 --> 00:46:53,400
Will you answer or not?

787
00:46:53,920 --> 00:46:54,760
No?

788
00:46:55,280 --> 00:46:56,480
Petch!

789
00:46:56,560 --> 00:46:58,120
- Ouch!
- Dao!

790
00:46:59,840 --> 00:47:01,040
Are you okay?

791
00:47:03,360 --> 00:47:04,360
Let's run!

792
00:47:04,440 --> 00:47:06,920
- I was clumsy.
- Hurry!

793
00:47:08,000 --> 00:47:09,440
Are you all right?

794
00:47:10,560 --> 00:47:11,760
Worry about yourself first.

795
00:47:13,280 --> 00:47:14,640
Let me see.

796
00:47:18,640 --> 00:47:19,480
Hey.

797
00:47:20,160 --> 00:47:21,440
Did you sprain your ankle?

798
00:47:25,360 --> 00:47:26,400
Okay.

799
00:47:27,240 --> 00:47:30,120
It's just a scrape and a little blood.

800
00:47:30,920 --> 00:47:31,840
I'll patch it up for you.

801
00:47:48,440 --> 00:47:50,200
- Are you ready?
- Yes.

802
00:47:51,800 --> 00:47:53,280
Ouch!

803
00:47:53,360 --> 00:47:54,440
Are you hurt?

804
00:47:55,160 --> 00:47:56,120
A little.

805
00:47:58,520 --> 00:47:59,680
Pain, pain…

806
00:48:01,080 --> 00:48:02,040
go away!

807
00:48:05,520 --> 00:48:06,800
Get better soon.

808
00:48:28,480 --> 00:48:29,560
All done.

809
00:48:30,360 --> 00:48:33,920
Now, don't let the wound get wet,
or it might get infected.

810
00:48:35,920 --> 00:48:37,360
Thanks a lot, Petch.

811
00:48:42,120 --> 00:48:43,160
- Ouch!
- Hey!

812
00:48:44,600 --> 00:48:45,520
Are you all right?

813
00:48:46,680 --> 00:48:47,920
I'm fine.

814
00:48:48,000 --> 00:48:49,400
I can walk.

815
00:48:49,480 --> 00:48:51,120
I don't want to be a burden to anyone.

816
00:48:52,400 --> 00:48:53,520
Are you being sarcastic?

817
00:48:54,240 --> 00:48:55,640
Who would dare?

818
00:48:56,240 --> 00:48:57,360
Stop being stubborn.

819
00:48:58,600 --> 00:48:59,760
Let's just say

820
00:48:59,840 --> 00:49:02,080
I'm more than happy to help you out.

821
00:49:04,240 --> 00:49:06,280
What the hell are you doing? Put me down!

822
00:49:06,360 --> 00:49:08,800
- Put me down!
- Keep moving, and I'll do worse.

823
00:49:11,840 --> 00:49:13,400
Where did you park your car?

824
00:49:14,400 --> 00:49:15,840
At the entrance of the alley.

825
00:49:15,920 --> 00:49:17,080
Okay.

826
00:49:17,160 --> 00:49:19,400
I'll offer you a free chauffeur service
straight to your house.

827
00:49:32,520 --> 00:49:33,480
You're only tough in a pack!

828
00:49:33,560 --> 00:49:34,840
Hit him!

829
00:49:35,800 --> 00:49:37,800
Natedao is my fiancée.

830
00:49:37,880 --> 00:49:39,800
You have no right to take her anywhere!

831
00:49:39,880 --> 00:49:40,840
NEXT EPISODE

832
00:49:40,920 --> 00:49:42,600
When you're with Petch,

833
00:49:43,120 --> 00:49:44,640
do you act innocent like this?

834
00:49:44,720 --> 00:49:45,640
Hey.

835
00:49:50,760 --> 00:49:51,840
It's completely ruined.

836
00:49:51,920 --> 00:49:53,920
Which bastard broke Petch's guitar?

837
00:49:59,320 --> 00:50:00,840
How could you do that to Dao?

838
00:50:12,720 --> 00:50:17,880
<i>I wish I knew if I ever crossed your mind</i>

839
00:50:18,960 --> 00:50:23,920
<i>I wish I knew if you heard the whisper</i>

840
00:50:24,880 --> 00:50:30,840
<i>For my heart is crying out my love</i>
<i>It's deep and true</i>

841
00:50:30,920 --> 00:50:35,840
<i>But never reaching you</i>

842
00:50:36,800 --> 00:50:42,040
<i>I know that it simply cannot be</i>

843
00:50:43,000 --> 00:50:48,000
<i>And I never want to cause you misery</i>

844
00:50:49,320 --> 00:50:54,640
<i>I'm just an ordinary man</i>
<i>Worth nothing at all</i>

845
00:50:54,720 --> 00:51:00,680
<i>And I never want to make</i>
<i>Your teardrops fall</i>

846
00:51:01,760 --> 00:51:06,240
<i>You are out of reach</i>

847
00:51:06,960 --> 00:51:11,800
<i>Is it a crime that I need you?</i>

848
00:51:14,040 --> 00:51:18,120
<i>Please let me know for sure</i>

849
00:51:19,000 --> 00:51:24,080
<i>That you're the one I've been waiting for</i>

850
00:51:25,040 --> 00:51:29,880
<i>How much longer can I bear this pain?</i>

851
00:51:31,040 --> 00:51:35,520
<i>How much longer must I wait in vain?</i>

852
00:51:36,680 --> 00:51:42,800
<i>I really don't know what move to make</i>

853
00:51:42,880 --> 00:51:48,120
<i>To end this heartache</i>
<i>And say that I love you</i>

854
00:51:48,200 --> 00:51:50,360
Subtitle translation by: Sarunpon T.
